    "body": "Reimplement vim.wait in Lua using new vim._loop_poll,\r\nvim._check_interrupt, and vim._ui_flush bindings.\r\n\r\nSimplified the wait loop by replacing the single long\r\nLOOP_PROCESS_EVENTS_UNTIL call plus a dummy timer with repeated\r\n_loop_poll(interval) calls. Each poll blocks for up to the interval and\r\nreturns on any event, so the periodic wakeups (and early wakeups on\r\nevents) fall out naturally without a timer, while keeping the same\r\ncondition‑check cadence.\r\n\r\nFix docs to state that success returns true plus the remaining callback\r\nresults (i.e., the callback’s second return value becomes the second\r\nreturn value from vim.wait).\r\n\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n- [x] Can `vim._ui_flush()` be replaced with `vim.api.nvim__redraw({flush=True})` or similar?\n  - No but could be added to nvim__redraw as an option. Keeping binding for now.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Can vim._ui_flush() be replaced with vim.api.nvim__redraw({flush=True}) or similar?\r\n\r\nThe existing `flush` would update pending window updates, which I think is unwanted here. `nvim__redraw` intentionally didn't expose `ui_flush()`. Could still be added as `ui_flush` or something if there is a need for it. IDK if that is preferred over what you have here.",
            "created_at": "2026-03-01T13:04:11Z",
